import React from 'react';

const CricketBallIcon = () => {
  return (
    <svg
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      width="48"
      height="48"
      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
      fill="none"
      className="cricket-ball-icon"
    >
      {/* Outer circle representing the cricket ball */}
      <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" fill="#4caf50" stroke="#388e3c" strokeWidth="2" />
      
      {/* Glossy effect */}
      <circle cx="16" cy="8" r="4" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.2)" />
      
      {/* Main seam across the middle */}
      <path
        d="M4 12c4 4 8 4 12 0"
        stroke="white"
        strokeWidth="2"
        strokeLinecap="round"
      />
      
      {/* Additional seams to represent the stitched threads */}
      <path
        d="M4 9.5c4 4 8 4 12 0M4 14.5c4 4 8 4 12 0"
        stroke="white"
        strokeWidth="2"
        strokeLinecap="round"
      />
      
      {/* Cricket Bat */}
      <rect
        x="8"
        y="15"
        width="8"
        height="5"
        fill="#795548"
        stroke="#5d4037"
        strokeWidth="1"
        rx="2"
      />
      <rect
        x="10"
        y="12"
        width="4"
        height="3"
        fill="#6d4c41"
        stroke="#4e342e"
        strokeWidth="1"
        rx="1.5"
      />
      <path
        d="M10 12l-2-3l2-1l2 1l-2 3z"
        fill="#3e2723"
        stroke="#2c211d"
        strokeWidth="1"
      />
    </svg>
  );
};

export default CricketBallIcon;
